Overview

Cedron Creek Campground is located on Whitney Lake on the main channel of the Brazos River in Central Texas. Over two million people visit Whitney Lake each year to enjoy the plethora of outdoor recreation opportunities and scenic beauty the lake provides.

Natural Features:

Cedron Creek is situated on the lakeshore among rolling hills covered with cedar, Live and Post oak.

Recreation:

Boating, fishing, swimming, canoeing and kayaking are popular activities at Whitney Lake. Anglers can fish for a variety of bass, crappie and catfish.

Facilities:

The campground offers 45 family sites and one group site with water and electric hookups. Amenities include flush toilets, recently renovated shower buildings, drinking water, a dump station, boat ramp, picnic pavilion and playground.

Nearby Attractions:

The 12.5 mile Hopewell Trail is nearby. It allows hiking, mountain biking, and horseback riding. Visitors can choose to travel north on the trail to Kimball Bend Park, or south to Lakeside Village and Powelldale Mountain.
properties.FacilityDirections: From I-35 in Hillsboro, take HWY 22 west, continue 12 miles to Whitney. At Whitney, take HWY 933 north for 3 miles, turn left on FM 1713 and cross the bridge, over the lake. Cedron is the first road on the left. Follow signs into the campground.
